
# Implementation-First Thinking

A roadmap exists to describe how software becomes more capable over time.

A milestone is justified only if completing it causes the software itself to become meaningfully more capable.

Examples of capability include:

* new runtime behavior
* new user-visible functionality
* new API surface
* new persistence capability
* new execution flow
* new integration
* new validation behavior
* new state transition
* new compiler or tooling behavior
* new platform capability
* new diagnostic capability
* new testing capability that constrains implementation behavior

Improved organization, clearer architecture, simpler code, or cleaner abstractions are valuable when they directly support implemented capability.

They are not milestones by themselves.

